<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-04-21T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-04-21T19:00:00-05:00" n="884" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d884">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">623.3531/4–747: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Peru</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-04-21T19:00:00-05:00">April 21,
                                    1947—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>193. <gloss target="#t_urtel1">Urtel</gloss> 263 Apr 7. <gloss target="#t_Agri1">Agri</gloss> officials verify that soft wheat
                            could be bought on West Coast at cost including transportation $105 long
                            ton but point out cost #2 hard wheat bought Kansas City would come to
                            about $123. Relative cost to Peru of <gloss target="#t_Arg1">Arg</gloss>
                            and US wheat would presumably have to take into account matter of
                            quality.</p>
                        <p>Position on question shipment wheat US to Peru has not changed from that
                            communicated in <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 152 Mar 15
                                [<hi rend="italic">25</hi>]. Third quarter allocations have also not
                            yet been considered for any country and will not be developed until
                            after recommendations have been developed with regard world distribution
                            pattern in <gloss target="#t_IEFC1">IEFC</gloss>.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>